caption: Tons of spices, frozen naan, fresh paneer, and a small but great selection of fresh produce (curry leaves, green chiles, mint)! The samosas are also amazing (and cheap!). I don’t review places often, but we love this shop!!

Used to be a lovely shop, with a good selection. However, the female owner is always rude and unfriendly and acts as if you are an imposition on her, even if you are a regular customer. The covid protocols are weak as they force all customers to use the same basket at checkout, with a view to only protecting themselves rather than the community. It’s a shame - could have been a nice neighbourhood spot. Takeout food was also average and overpriced.

Prices are great for an awesome selection of food. Things like dried spices, dried lentils and other proteins, rice, breads, canned sauces and foods, and even Indian snacks. Cant wait to go back to get more.
Small shop with lots of Indian spices and specialties. Staff is very friendly! Will visit again.
Awesome grocery store run by some wonderful people

Small but packed full of every ingredient you need to make yummy Indian food at home. The owners were super friendly and helpful showing me where each type of item was kept, and they sell warm, delicious samosas in the store!
Very crowded, hard to maintain social distancing

Very rude customer service.  We had bought an item that turn out to be of bad quality, when we told them that item wasn't good (so they are aware) they instead responded very rudely. During pandemic, people should be cooperative, showing attitude to other people is not what this world needs right now. It is a shame really.
I had an extraordinary time at this spot. We loved the nice atmosphere and the meals. The staff are super affable. I am content we finally managed to visit this place.
Come here at least every other week for spices and delicious samosas. Owners are extremely nice and they have everything you could ever need in stock :)
(Translated by Google) Worst papadi chat  (Original) Worst papadi chat

Best place to go for those Indian ingredients that are hard to find or are way overpriced at a regular super market. The owners are always very nice and helpful. The chaat is so good I sometimes just go for it alone.

Great service, delicious chaat.  I called on the phone to order some fresh food (chaats and samosas) as well as some groceries.  The lady I spoke with was very patient and took my order and payment by telephone. When I drove up,I called and they quickly put everything in my car.  For Bethesda, the prices were certainly fair, and everything was delicious.  They also offer delivery for a fee.
Expensive,
Very clean, well stock and reasonable price. I recommend 100% to anyone wants fresh vegetables and quality groceries and friendly staff.

Amazing. The owners are so friendly, and my whole family knows them. There is such a big selection of indian groceries for such a small shop. Also don’t forget to try their samosas, they are delicious!

Have good selection of products, however cost 30-40% higher than normal Indian grocery store. I brought few items from there today and left with a feeling that I was cheated. I would only go there if I need to buy any last min items and willing to pay high cost.
Great family owned shop. The owners were very friendly and they make the best Samosas that I have had!

Exceptionally great selection of everything Indian. Mr Deepak and his wife make sure they order the best brands and products in every category of Indian food products. Save a long trip to an Indian story far away. Avoid Dana Bazaar and go to Guru. You won’t be disappointed. Also try their delicious samosas!
I prefer this venue a lot. It has a very nice air. The meals are marvelous. the service is powerful and the team is very professional. The pay is decent. very much recommend.
They had a good collection of south indian snacks. The vegetables were fresh. We will be going back!
Stuff are unfriendly and pushy also overpriced. When I go there all the time a lady watching me . It was uncomfortable.
Please be prepared to pay apprx 20% higher than any gaithersburg or rockville  indian stores
Great neighborhood market with delightful proprietors. Particularly love their samosas, fresh ginger, and frozen naan - but really, everything I’ve gotten there is good.
Really enjoyed the chaat here and will be back to try more.
Delicious samosas!

It’s a very good indian grocery store. Only thing is few items are little expensive. Shop owners are very friendly. I would suggest to owners to earn money to make regular customers not by selling expensive items.
Very friendly owners, decent groceries. The real gems.are the chaat and the homemade frozen meals.
Nice market.  Good variety.  Employees super friendly and helpful.  Worth the trip

Great Indian grocery store with all the essentials. Very friendly staff and owners. They also make homemade Indian food you can order in advance (pre-made and chilled not takeout). But the fresh samosas are always ready to eat.
I am by no means an Indian grocery expert but, they certainly had everything I was looking for and the staff was very friendly. Will definitely be back!
One of the best place for Indian groceries in Bethesda.
Great collection of groceries and super nice owners
One and only Indian grocery store available in Bethesda.. You will get all that you are looking for. Very much appreciated the way they are maintaining.
Lovely little Indian grocer and snack shop with an impressive variety of both packaged and fresh prepared foods.

Wow, a big, bright, and well-stocked Indian grocery store right right near work! I no longer have to go hunting for my favorite ethnic foods, with a Japanese grocery store (Hinata) on one side of the street and now Guru on the same block. You can get home-cooked meals (frozen but can easily be heated up in a pot), fresh samosas and even superb fresh chai (sorry, Starbucks, we are breaking up or at least cooling off). And snacks of all kinds. Half the time, I don't know what I'm eating but the Indian flavors are so addictive! Bonus: the proprietors are so friendly and nice, they've made their store my new haunt and zen place to step away from the office. :-)
Really good authentic Indian supplies. Great place
Excellent selection of products and very friendly and helpful owners!

Great new addition to Bethesda! Most Indian grocery items available - if any item is unavailable in-store, the friendly owners order it in promptly. We also enjoy the savory chaat items to snack on during our weekend Indian shopping visits. Most importantly, saves us a long trip to Indian stores further out in the burbs.

Wonderful store! Tons of different products from different dals and spices to desserts and ready made meals. The perfect store If you ever need anything for a recipe or a quick meal or snack! The owner was very nice and helped me pick out some spices for my red lentil dal.
Best chat (Indian) food! - I come down from Potomac to eat here. He used to be off of Travilah road

Lovely little Indian grocery store.  Well-stocked, with very friendly and helpful management & workers.  Everyone, please give them your business - I need this shop to stay open so I can keep going there!
What a nice new store. Great place to buy Indian ingredients. Nice snacks and food. We are partial to kulfi ice scream. Finally, the owners are lovely and always helpful.
good stuff at good prices.
Great selection at good price and really nice owners!
Excellent chaat, and very friendly and helpful owners.

Smallish selection due to the small store.  Chaat plates look delicious and fairly priced.  Produce selection is small but looked very fresh.  Outstanding customer service which, sadly, has never been my experience before in Indian groceries.  Please keep up the good work!
Finally, an Indian grocer I don't have to drive so far out of the way to get to! The owners are very nice and the chaat is great.

Super excited for these guys. I think it's a surefire winner. Simple concept really—-shop the full range Indian groceries and have some amazing Chaat while you're at it!  As far as groceries are concerned they have everything you need except perhaps some fresh produce. Not a big deal IMO. Prices are less than Dana Bazaar in Rockville so that's a plus. The Chaat was in fact stellar. A little on the pricey compared to most restaurants in the area perhaps , but there really was a ton of food on my plate. Realistically it's for 2 to share IMO. Authentic "Street Chaat" taste to boot and made fresh to order right in front of you---no mystery ingredients I can assure you!  Try it all —— but the Bhel puri (ask for it a little spicy) & the Papri Chaat are bonafide must haves.  Off you go to the Gurus of Chaat!!
Great owners - very friendly and helpful!
Perfect place for Indian groceries and very inviting shopping owner.

This is a very clean and well stocked Indian market located in North Potomac. They carry famous brands of single and mixed spices that are imported from India. You can find all kinds of ready-made food in the freezer in the back of the store and all kinds of sweets and desserts in the freezer in front of the store. There is a single table and 2 chairs in front of the store by the register. They serve Limited items of food that you could set there and eat. I was told that they carry the best varieties of mango however when we got there in early September the mango season had just ended. the owner / manager was very friendly and helpful.  I felt very welcomed here. There is also a Sikh temple within a block from this store. I will be going back and highly recommend this place.
Friendly staff. Small but carries a wide variety of different things.
Highly over priced. Do not try the chaat.
Love the Chaat. I eat here at least once a week. Good selection of groceries. Owners very pleasant.

Overpriced (if not in a hurry, you are better off going to Lotte on Muddy Branch Road). Owner is nice and friendly, and this is a good place when you need Indian things in a hurry and don't want to drive to the regular Indian grocery stores.
always have what I need, great chaat, and friendly staff
Great placer to have a quick coca cola.
Good selection, surprised they didn't carry milk The chaat they make there is also good.
Many varieties but a more expensive than other comparable Indian grocery stores.
Convenient location,, great chaat no wait time!!!
Very clean!
Friendly neighborhood grocer.
Best Indian grocery store I've been to. Lots of hard to find spices, well organized, and clean. Friendly and helpful staff. They even have samosa and chaat if you need a snack.
very  friendly owner and helpful. Haven't had a bad experience here at all. Always willing to chat and answer questions.  Very good chaat choices as well
a very friendly neighborhood indian/asian grocery store with great service and reasonable rates
